title.en: Offshore Wind Power Platform Ontology for OPTiMAR
title.es: Ontología de Plataforma Eólica Offshore para OPTiMAR

description.en: This ontology describes the components, failures, sensors, and events related to offshore wind platforms.
description.es: Esta ontología describe los componentes, fallos, sensores y eventos relacionados con las plataformas eólicas offshore.

comments.en:
Version 2.1 (2026-01-19) - Sensor expansion, completeness and robustness improvements:
    - Added component classes: Gearbox, Transformer
    - Added electrical sensor classes: ActivePowerSensor, ReactivePowerSensor, CurrentSensor, VoltageSensor, GridFrequencySensor, TorqueSensor
    - Added specific data classes: ElectricalData, TemperatureData, RotorData and their subclasses
    - Added general TemperatureSensor class to measure temperature of components and environment
    - Added optimar:measuresTemperatureOf property to relate temperature sensors with components or environmental conditions
    - Added inverse properties for sensors: temperatureMonitoredBy, electricalParameterMonitoredBy, rotorParameterMonitoredBy
    - Added rotor sensor classes: RotorSensor, RotorSpeedSensor, RotorAngleSensor
    - Added ElectricalSensor base class to group electrical sensors
    - Added severity property to model failure criticality
    - Added OperationalState class for detailed operational states
    - Added temporal properties: startDateTime, endDateTime, detectionDateTime, duration
    - Added failure relationships: causesFailure, precededBy
    - Fixed syntax errors
comments.es:
Version 2.1 (2026-01-19) - Ampliación de sensores, mejoras de completud y robustez:
    - Añadidas clases de componentes: Gearbox, Transformer
    - Añadidas clases de sensores eléctricos: ActivePowerSensor, ReactivePowerSensor, CurrentSensor, VoltageSensor, GridFrequencySensor, TorqueSensor
    - Añadidas clases de datos específicas: ElectricalData, TemperatureData, RotorData y sus subclases
    - Añadida clase TemperatureSensor general para medir temperatura de componentes y ambiente
    - Añadida propiedad optimar:measuresTemperatureOf para relacionar sensores de temperatura con componentes o condiciones ambientales
    - Añadidas propiedades inversas para sensores: temperatureMonitoredBy, electricalParameterMonitoredBy, rotorParameterMonitoredBy
    - Añadidas clases de sensores de rotor: RotorSensor, RotorSpeedSensor, RotorAngleSensor
    - Añadida clase base ElectricalSensor para agrupar sensores eléctricos
    - Añadida propiedad severity para modelar criticidad de fallos
    - Añadida clase OperationalState para estados operativos detallados
    - Añadidas propiedades temporales: startDateTime, endDateTime, detectionDateTime, duration
    - Añadidas relaciones entre fallos: causesFailure, precededBy
    - Corregidos errores sintácticos

abstract.value: Ontología que modela los elementos estructurales, sensores, eventos y fallos de plataformas eólicas offshore, incluyendo datos de medición, actores involucrados y relaciones semánticas entre componentes. Compatible con SOSA para observaciones y QUDT para unidades de medida.

Ontology modeling structural elements, sensors, events, and failures in floating offshore wind platforms, including measurement data, involved actors, and semantic relationships between components. Compatible with SOSA for observations and QUDT for units of measure.
